data.text:
It's official — after over a year of rumors, Camp Rock 2 is ready to, well, rock! It was just announced today that the title will be Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam and the Jonas Brothers and Demi Lovato are set to reprise their roles at the band Connect 3 and Mitchie Torres. Meaghan Martin, Alyson Stoner, Anna Maria Perez de Tagle, and Roshon Fegan have also signed on for the second movie.

Here's the deal: The campers will return to Camp Rock for another summer –Â but this time there will be a rival camp, Camp Star, that has taken some of Camp Rock's staff and campers! Camp Star's big shot, Luke (played by Matthew "Mdot" Finley), will challenge Camp Rock to a huge showdown to see which camp really is the most talented.

And if that wasn't enough drama, Nick's character, Nate, will have a love interest this movie! He's going to fall hard for the owner of Camp Star's daughter, Dana (played by Chloe Bridges).

Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam is set to premiere in the summer of 2010!

Are you guys excited? Why or why not?

For even more dish on CR 2 (Are Demi and Joe going fall in love this time around?!), make sure to get

J-14's August issue on stands now!
